The paper discusses the use of interference to improve wireless secrecy, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves designing transceivers for legitimate partners, which is related to network infrastructure (cs.NI). The issue of eavesdropping and security is a common concern in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions simulation, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed algorithm involves optimizing network performance, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
